  "title": "ISic001170. Funerary inscription for Herais",
  "body": "<div id=\"editions\"><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Valentina Mignosa, Alex Antoniou</div><div id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  <span class=\"textpartnumber\" id=\"aba\">section a</span>  <div class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"diva--interpretive\">  <span class=\"textpartnumber\" style=\"left: -4em;\">Col. 1<br></span>  <a id=\"aa-l1-interpretive\"><!--0--></a><span class=\"linenumber\">1</span>[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>] <span data-text=\"ων\" data-n=\"10\" data-lemma=\"NOLEMMA\">ω̣ν̣</span>  <br id=\"aa-l2-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">2</span>[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>] <span data-text=\"ου\" data-n=\"20\" data-lemma=\"NOLEMMA\">ο̣υ</span>  <br id=\"aa-l3-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">3</span>[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>] <span data-text=\"λε\" data-n=\"30\" data-lemma=\"NOLEMMA\">λε</span>  <br id=\"aa-l4-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">4</span><span data-text=\"χαῖρε\" data-n=\"35\" data-lemma=\"χαίρω\">[χαῖ]ρ̣ε</span>  </span></div>  <span class=\"textpartnumber\" id=\"abb\">section b</span>  <div class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"divb--interpretive\">  <span class=\"textpartnumber\" style=\"left: -4em;\">Col. 2<br></span>  <a id=\"ab-l1-interpretive\"><!--0--></a><span class=\"linenumber\">1</span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Ἡραΐ\n                        Ἡρύλου\n                        θυγάτηρ\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Ἡραΐ\"><span data-text=\"Ἡραΐ\" data-n=\"40\" data-lemma=\"Ἡραΐς\">Ἡραΐ</span></span>  <br id=\"ab-l2-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">2</span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Ἡρύλου\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"patronym\" data-text=\"Ἡρύλου\"><span data-text=\"Ἡρύλου\" data-n=\"45\" data-lemma=\"Ἡρυλος\">Ἡρύλου</span></span></span>  <br id=\"ab-l3-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">3</span><span data-text=\"θυγάτηρ\" data-n=\"50\" data-lemma=\"θυγάτηρ\">θυγάτηρ</span></span>  <br id=\"ab-l4-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">4</span><span data-text=\"χαῖρε\" data-n=\"55\" data-lemma=\"χαίρω\">χαῖρε</span>  </span></div>  <p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Victoria Fendel, Robert Crellin</div><div id=\"edition-interpretive-simple-lemmatized\">  <span class=\"textpartnumber\" id=\"aba\">section a</span>  <div class=\"textpart\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"diva--interpretive\"> [<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>] <span data-text=\"ων\" data-n=\"10\" data-lemma=\"NOLEMMA\">ων</span> [<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>] <span data-text=\"ου\" data-n=\"20\" data-lemma=\"NOLEMMA\">ου</span> [<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>] <span data-text=\"λε\" data-n=\"30\" data-lemma=\"NOLEMMA\">λε</span>  <span data-text=\"χαῖρε\" data-n=\"35\" data-lemma=\"χαίρω\">χαῖρε</span>  </span></div>  <span class=\"textpartnumber\" id=\"abb\">section b</span>  <div class=\"textpart\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"divb--interpretive\">  <span data-text=\"Ἡραΐ\" data-n=\"40\" data-lemma=\"Ἡραΐς\">Ἡραΐ</span>  <span data-text=\"Ἡρύλου\" data-n=\"45\" data-lemma=\"Ἡρυλος\">Ἡρύλου</span>  <span data-text=\"θυγάτηρ\" data-n=\"50\" data-lemma=\"θυγάτηρ\">θυγάτηρ</span>  <span data-text=\"χαῖρε\" data-n=\"55\" data-lemma=\"χαίρω\">χαῖρε</span>  </span></div>  <p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Valentina Mignosa, Alex Antoniou</div><div id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\"><span class=\"textpartnumber\" id=\"aba\">section a</span><div class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"diva--diplomatic\"><span class=\"textpartnumber\" style=\"left: -4em;\">Col. 1<br></span><a id=\"aa-l1-diplomatic\"><!--0--></a><span class=\"linenumber\">1</span>[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]<span data-text=\"ων\" data-n=\"10\" data-lemma=\"NOLEMMA\">..</span><br id=\"aa-l2-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">2</span>[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]<span data-text=\"ου\" data-n=\"20\" data-lemma=\"NOLEMMA\">.Υ</span><br id=\"aa-l3-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">3</span>[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]<span data-text=\"λε\" data-n=\"30\" data-lemma=\"NOLEMMA\">ΛΕ</span><br id=\"aa-l4-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">4</span><span data-text=\"χαῖρε\" data-n=\"35\" data-lemma=\"χαίρω\">[...].Ε</span></span></div><span class=\"textpartnumber\" id=\"abb\">section b</span><div class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"divb--diplomatic\"><span class=\"textpartnumber\" style=\"left: -4em;\">Col. 2<br></span><a id=\"ab-l1-diplomatic\"><!--0--></a><span class=\"linenumber\">1</span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Ἡραΐ\n                        Ἡρύλου\n                        θυγάτηρ\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Ἡραΐ\"><span data-text=\"Ἡραΐ\" data-n=\"40\" data-lemma=\"Ἡραΐς\">ΗΡΑΙ</span></span><br id=\"ab-l2-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">2</span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Ἡρύλου\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"patronym\" data-text=\"Ἡρύλου\"><span data-text=\"Ἡρύλου\" data-n=\"45\" data-lemma=\"Ἡρυλος\">ΗΡΥΛΟΥ</span></span></span><br id=\"ab-l3-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">3</span><span data-text=\"θυγάτηρ\" data-n=\"50\" data-lemma=\"θυγάτηρ\">ΘΥΓΑΤΗΡ</span></span><br id=\"ab-l4-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">4</span><span data-text=\"χαῖρε\" data-n=\"55\" data-lemma=\"χαίρω\">ΧΑΙΡΕ</span></span></div><p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Victoria Fendel, Robert Crellin</div><div id=\"edition-diplomatic-simple-lemmatized\"><span class=\"textpartnumber\" id=\"aba\">section a</span><div class=\"textpart\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"diva--diplomatic\">[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]<span data-text=\"ων\" data-n=\"10\" data-lemma=\"NOLEMMA\">ΩΝ</span>[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]<span data-text=\"ου\" data-n=\"20\" data-lemma=\"NOLEMMA\">ΟΥ</span>[<span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]<span data-text=\"λε\" data-n=\"30\" data-lemma=\"NOLEMMA\">ΛΕ</span><span data-text=\"χαῖρε\" data-n=\"35\" data-lemma=\"χαίρω\">ΧΑΙΡΕ</span></span></div><span class=\"textpartnumber\" id=\"abb\">section b</span><div class=\"textpart\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"divb--diplomatic\"><span data-text=\"Ἡραΐ\" data-n=\"40\" data-lemma=\"Ἡραΐς\">ΗΡΑΙ</span><span data-text=\"Ἡρύλου\" data-n=\"45\" data-lemma=\"Ἡρυλος\">ΗΡΥΛΟΥ</span><span data-text=\"θυγάτηρ\" data-n=\"50\" data-lemma=\"θυγάτηρ\">ΘΥΓΑΤΗΡ</span><span data-text=\"χαῖρε\" data-n=\"55\" data-lemma=\"χαίρω\">ΧΑΙΡΕ</span></span></div><p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div></div>  <div id=\"facsimile-images\"><h2>Facsimile Images</h2><a href=\"ISic001170_tiled.tif\"><img title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic001170_tiled-thumb.tif\"></a><a href=\"ISic001170.jpg\"><img title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic001170-thumb.jpg\"></a></div>  <div id=\"apparatus\"><h4>Apparatus criticus</h4><ul><li><span>  <span>Text after autopsy</span>  </span></li></ul></div>  <div id=\"translation\"><h2>English translation</h2><p class=\"translation-author\"><a href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0001-7077-0703\">Alex Antoniou</a></p>  <p>[Right column]: Herais, daughter of Herylos, farewell.</p>  </div>  <div id=\"commentary\"><h2>commentary</h2>  <p>Given the presence of at least two epitaphs, it is likely that this plaque belonged to a family tomb. Herylos is a unique name, not attested elsewhere. Brugnone (1974) suggests that it could be a form of the documented Heryllos, or is a derivative of the Latin Herylus. Herais is an extremely common name in the empire, attested in Sicily only in the masculine on a lead sheet at Kamarina, <a href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic030053\" target=\"_blank\">ISic030053</a>.</p>  </div>  <div id=\"bibliography\"><h2>bibliography</h2>  <ul><li> Manni Piraino 1971 185 no.1 tav.55.1 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001774\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001774</a>  </li><li> Brugnone 1974 9 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001397\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001397</a>  </li></ul>  <ul><li></li></ul>  </div>  <div id=\"handnote\"> <p>Letters are neat, evenly spaced, but finely incised on stone. Letters bear simple serifs. Epsilons have arrows in place of cross-bar. Short cross-bar of the theta in column 2, line 3.</p> Line 1  27-28  Line 2  27-29  Line 3  23-28  Line 4  26-28  Interlineation line 1 to 2    </div><div id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. </div>",
